pes (kubernetes/api/core/v1/types.go) import metav1 via:\n```go\nimport metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n```\n\nEach type embeds both:\n```go\nmetav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\nmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\" protobuf:\"...\"`\n```\n\n### Step 3: Scheme Registration\nThe core/v1 register.go file (kubernetes/api/core/v1/register.go) defines the addKnownTypes function that calls:\n```go\nscheme.AddKnownTypes(SchemeGroupVersion, &Pod{}, &PodList{}, ...)\n```\n\nThis function uses SchemeBuilder pattern defined in:\n- kubernetes/kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/scheme_builder.go\n\n### Step 4: Scheme Implementation\nThe Scheme type (kubernetes/kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/scheme.go) implements AddKnownTypes method which:\n- Takes variadic runtime.Object arguments (the interface type)\n- Registers each type with the scheme for serialization/deserialization\n- Requires all types to implement the Object interface\n\n### Step 5: Installation into Global Scheme\nThe kubernetes/kubernetes/pkg/apis/core/install/install.go file registers types into the global legacyscheme by calling:\n```go\ncore.AddToScheme(scheme)  // Internal core types\nv1.AddToScheme(scheme)    // v1 types from kubernetes/api\n```\n\nThis chain ensures that all core/v1 types implementing runtime.Object are available for:\n- Serialization to JSON/YAML/Protobuf\n- Deserialization from external formats\n- Type conversions\n- Watch operations\n- API client operations\n\n## Import Flow Summary\n1. kubernetes/api/core/v1/types.go → imports → k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1 (TypeMeta, ObjectMeta)\n2. kubernetes/api/core/v1/register.go → imports → k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime (Scheme, Object interface)\n3. kubernetes/kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/interfaces.go → defines Object interface\n4. kubernetes/kubernetes/pkg/apis/core/install/install.go → registers all types into the global scheme"
